  "prompt": "Is it true that we fantasize about friends of opposite gender?",
  "response": "Many people do experience fantasies about friends of the opposite gender at some point. These thoughts can be influenced by various factors, including attraction, emotional connection, and the dynamics of the friendship. Fantasizing about friends can be a normal part of human sexuality and can stem from curiosity, desire, or simply the nature of the relationship.\n\nHowever, the extent and nature of these fantasies can vary widely among individuals. Some people might find themselves drawn to friends in a romantic or sexual way, while others might maintain a more platonic perspective. It's also important to note that acting on these fantasies can have implications for the friendship and should be approached with consideration for the feelings of both parties involved.",
